#Basic lua knowledge
in your base init.lua script when you require something it looks in the lua folder as a base directory. Then you can separate folders and lua files with . like lazyvim.util. If the folder has a init.lua file in it then the last part of the path can be the name of the folder otherwise you need to have the last part of the path be the name of the lua file

#great example to show off how to use lspconfig with lazy.nvim

https://gitlab.com/of_jorts/dotfiles/-/raw/main/nvim/.config/nvim/lua/plugins/lsp.lua?ref_type=heads

